  GIT
  ###
    Windows
    #######
    https://git-scm.com/ - URL to be used to download the GIT client
    Click Downloads --> Windows (Save the exe file. This file is used for installation)
      Installation instructions
      #########################
      1. Double click the .exe file downloaded
      2. Accept the License [Click "Next >"]
      3. Choose Components to be installed [Enable Additonal Icons, On the desktop. Click "Next >"]
      4. Choose the editor [vim is the default editor. Click "Next >"]
      5. Adjust PATH variable [Use Git from Git Bash only. Click "Next >"]
      6. Choose HTTPS transport backend [Use the OpenSSL library. Click "Next >"]
      7. Configure line ending conversions [Chekout windows style Commit Unix style. Click "Next >"]
      8. Configure terminal emulator [Use MinTTY. Click "Next >"]
      9. Configure extra options [Disable all. Click "Next >"]
      10. Click "Install"
